The paper discusses the challenge of achieving machine common sense, which is a fundamental problem in artificial intelligence. The paper also discusses two different strategies for addressing this challenge: one that focuses on learning from experience and one that focuses on learning from reading the web. These strategies involve machine learning, natural language processing, computer vision, and robotics, which are all subfields of computer science. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.RO (Robotics).
